Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of generalized degrees-of-freedom (GDoF) of downlink and uplink cellular networks, which are related to information theory and communication systems. The use of Gaussian interfering broadcast channels (IBC) and Gaussian interfering multiple access channels (IMAC) also suggests a focus on communication and networking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.COMM (Computer Communication and Networks), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
